  "prompt": "Do we have Financial Management in IPCC group 1 in may 2017? Websites show change in syllabus.",
  "response": "Yes, you are correct. The syllabus for the CA Intermediate (erstwhile IPCC) was revised by the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI) effective from 2017. \n\nFor the May 2017 attempt, the old syllabus was applicable, but changes were announced for subsequent sessions. Under the old syllabus, Financial Management was part of the IPCC Group 1, under the subject \"Cost Accounting and Financial Management\" (Paper 3).\n\nHowever, from July 1, 2017, onwards, the new syllabus came into effect, and the subjects were reorganized. Under the new syllabus, Financial Management is part of Paper 8: \"Financial Management and Economics for Finance\" in the CA Intermediate course, which falls under Group 2.\n\nSo, for the May 2017 session, Financial Management was indeed part of the IPCC Group 1 curriculum under the old syllabus. If you were planning to appear for exams after May 2017, you would need to follow the new syllabus and its corresponding subjects and groupings.",
